# Cloudflare Secrets Configuration

This file documents all secrets that need to be configured in Cloudflare dashboard.

## How to Set Secrets in Cloudflare

1. Go to Cloudflare Dashboard → Workers & Pages → CU Daters
2. Click "Settings" → "Variables"
3. Add each secret below under "Secrets" (encrypted)

## Required Secrets

### MongoDB Data API
```
MONGODB_DATA_API_KEY = "your-mongodb-data-api-key"
MONGODB_DATA_APP_ID = "your-data-api-app-id"
```

Get these from: MongoDB Cloud → App Services → Data API → API Keys

### Authentication
```
JWT_SECRET = "your-very-secure-jwt-secret-change-this-in-production"
JWT_EXPIRY = "7d"
ADMIN_PIN = "your-4-6-digit-pin-for-admin-operations"
```

### Payment Processing
```
RAZORPAY_KEY_ID = "rzp_live_xxxxx"
RAZORPAY_KEY_SECRET = "your-razorpay-secret-key"
```

### File Storage (R2)
```
R2_BUCKET = "campus-connect-uploads"
R2_ACCOUNT_ID = "your-cloudflare-account-id"
R2_ACCESS_KEY_ID = "your-r2-access-key"
R2_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY = "your-r2-secret-key"
```

### Environment
```
ENVIRONMENT = "production"
NODE_ENV = "production"
ALLOWED_ORIGINS = "https://your-domain.com,https://www.your-domain.com"
```

### Frontend URLs
```
FRONTEND_URL = "https://your-domain.com"
VITE_API_URL = "https://your-domain.com/api"
```

## Environment-Specific Setup

### Production Environment
```toml
[env.production.vars]
ENVIRONMENT = "production"
NODE_ENV = "production"
ALLOWED_ORIGINS = "https://your-domain.com"

[env.production.secrets]
MONGODB_DATA_API_KEY = "prod-key"
JWT_SECRET = "prod-secret"
# ... other secrets
```

### Staging Environment
```toml
[env.staging.vars]
ENVIRONMENT = "staging"
NODE_ENV = "staging"
ALLOWED_ORIGINS = "https://staging.your-domain.com"

[env.staging.secrets]
MONGODB_DATA_API_KEY = "staging-key"
JWT_SECRET = "staging-secret"
# ... other secrets
```

## Local Development (.env)

Create `.env.local` for local testing:

```env
# Development environment
NODE_ENV=development
ENVIRONMENT=development
VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:8787

# MongoDB (use sandbox for dev)
MONGODB_DATA_API_KEY=your-dev-key
MONGODB_DATA_APP_ID=your-dev-app-id

# JWT
JWT_SECRET=dev-secret-key-change-in-prod
JWT_EXPIRY=7d
ADMIN_PIN=1234

# Razorpay (use test keys)
RAZORPAY_KEY_ID=rzp_test_xxxxx
RAZORPAY_KEY_SECRET=test-secret

# R2 (optional for local dev)
R2_BUCKET=campus-connect-uploads-dev
```

## Security Best Practices

✅ **DO:**
- Use strong, random JWT_SECRET (minimum 32 characters)
- Rotate secrets regularly (monthly recommended)
- Use different keys for staging vs production
- Store backups of secrets in secure password manager
- Enable audit logs in Cloudflare

❌ **DON'T:**
- Commit secrets to GitHub (use GitHub Actions secrets)
- Share API keys in Discord/Slack
- Use same secret across environments
- Log sensitive data
- Hardcode secrets in function code

## GitHub Actions Secrets Setup

Add these to GitHub repository secrets (Settings → Secrets and variables):

```
CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN       # Your Cloudflare API token
CLOUDFLARE_ACCOUNT_ID      # Your Cloudflare Account ID

MONGODB_DATA_API_KEY       # Will be deployed to Cloudflare
JWT_SECRET                 # Will be deployed to Cloudflare
RAZORPAY_KEY_ID           # Will be deployed to Cloudflare
RAZORPAY_KEY_SECRET       # Will be deployed to Cloudflare
ADMIN_PIN                 # Will be deployed to Cloudflare

VITE_API_URL              # Frontend API URL
```

## Verifying Secrets are Loaded

Deploy a test function:

```javascript
// functions/api/debug-env.js
export async function onRequest(context) {
  // This function lists which env vars are present (not their values for security)
  return new Response(JSON.stringify({
    mongodb_configured: !!context.env.MONGODB_DATA_API_KEY,
    jwt_configured: !!context.env.JWT_SECRET,
    razorpay_configured: !!context.env.RAZORPAY_KEY_ID,
    admin_pin_configured: !!context.env.ADMIN_PIN,
    r2_configured: !!context.env.R2_BUCKET,
  }), {
    headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' }
  });
}
```

Then visit: `https://your-domain.com/api/debug-env`

Should show all `true` values if properly configured.
